The main flow is clear now: `route` checks only the router’s own end-token balance, and the Uniswap plugin is a `delegatecall` plugin that always directs swap proceeds to `address(this)`. I’m validating whether that makes user loss reachable as reported and whether any of the broader delegatecall claims are actually in-scope versus owner-trust assumptions.
